    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-200 mb-3">Pricing and Value for Money</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6">iTalki takes the lead on pricing, with community tutors available from as low as $5 per hour. This makes it one of the most affordable platforms for regular conversation practice. Verbling has a higher price floor, typically starting from $12 per hour, reflecting its focus on professional tutors. While both platforms let you book one-off lessons without a subscription, iTalki is the better choice if budget is your main priority. Verbling's higher prices tend to attract tutors with more formal credentials, so the value depends on whether you need professional-level instruction.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-200 mb-3">Tutor Selection and Availability</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6">Both platforms offer impressive tutor networks, with iTalki holding a slight edge in sheer volume. iTalki has over 10,000 tutors spread across all major time zones, making it easier to find a match at unusual hours. Verbling's network of around 10,000 tutors is more focused on professional educators with verified backgrounds. If you are looking for a specific time slot or a tutor with particular expertise, iTalki's scale gives it a practical advantage. Verbling is a strong option if you specifically want tutors with formal teaching credentials.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-200 mb-3">Lesson Quality and Structure</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6">iTalki separates its tutors into community tutors and professional teachers. Community tutors are ideal for casual conversation practice and are more affordable. Professional teachers on iTalki offer more structured lessons and have verified credentials. Verbling focuses exclusively on professional tutors, meaning every tutor on the platform has been vetted for teaching experience and credentials. This makes Verbling a more consistent experience, though it comes at a higher price. For structured learning goals such as exam prep or business English, both platforms have suitable options.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-200 mb-3">Platform Features</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6">iTalki offers a lesson recording and replay feature, which is particularly valuable for reviewing mistakes and tracking your progress over time. Verbling focuses on real-time conversation and does not offer lesson recording. Both platforms have mobile apps for iOS and Android, and both provide tools for scheduling and managing your lessons. iTalki's instant booking option is a standout feature that lets you find and book a tutor within minutes, which Verbling handles less efficiently. If recorded lessons and quick booking matter to you, iTalki has the edge.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-200 mb-3">Cancellation and Flexibility</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6">Both platforms offer flexible cancellation policies. iTalki allows cancellations up to 24 hours in advance for a full refund, with some tutors offering shorter notice windows. Verbling also lets you cancel lessons 12 to 24 hours before the scheduled time. Neither platform requires a subscription, so you can book lessons as needed without committing to a monthly plan. iTalki's wider tutor availability across time zones gives it an advantage when you need to reschedule at short notice.</p>
  </section>

